def factors(n):
    return reduce(list.__add__,
                ([i, n//i] for i in range(1, int(n**0.5) + 1) if n % i == 0))
t = long(raw_input())
while t:
    t-=1
    a = long(raw_input())
    b = []
    b = factors(a)
    b = list(set(b))
    b.sort()
    c = 1
    for i in xrange(len(b)-1):
        c*=b[i]
    c = str(c)
    print c[-4:]
